  "text": "Classic Loading. To receive its definitive prosthesis, loading must take place no less than 6 months after surgical insertion in the superior maxillary bone and 3 to 4 months in the inferior maxillary bone. [CITATION_1] Immediate Loading. To be considered an authentic immediate loading, loading must occur in the first 24 hours after insertion of the implant. A higher accumulation of proteins will be led by the application of moderate hydrostatic strengths, tensions, or compressions, leading to faster bone formation.",
